If the planned synergy between the pension fund operators and life insurers is anything to hope on, micro pension contributors will have cause to smile as the two service providers are mulling plans to incorporate health insurance cover into the Micro Pension Plan (MPP). Daily Independent gathered that the two sectors are already talking in a view to ensuring that the micro pension subscribers enjoys the health insurance cover as part of the package as Pension Fund Administrators (PFAs) and stakeholders in the pension industry have revealed plans toward achieving the milestone across the country. It is expected that the details of the package and how the MPP subscribers will benefit without incurring extra cost would soon be unveiled when the synergy is harmonised. Pension Fund Index Posts Hope For Investors In 2022 China Opens Borders For International Re-Insurance Brokers Disclosing this in Lagos recently, the Pension Fund Operators Association of Nigeria (PenOp), said the gesture would lead to insurance for the unemployed and would attract people in the informal sector. Idu Okwuosa, the Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer, Access Pension Fund Custodian, as well as the Head of Media Committee of PenOp, said the industry was working with insurance operators to come up with incentives for micro-pension contributions. Okwuosa called on operators and the National Pension Commission (PenCom) to design lifestyle products for micro pension contributors and also work together to see besides benefits of retirement and contingency savings, contributors maximise other robust incentives. According to her, some pension operators had visited markets such as the Alaba International Market to enlighten traders on the need to save and plan for retirement through the MPP.